\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.7465257313764008, \"rank\": 0.33271919788371584, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Pierre holds the United States indoor mile and 3,000-meter records and is the reigning 3,000-meter world champion.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999829392776261, \"rank\": 0.00011142267478611814, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She qualified for the 2024 Olympics in the 1,500-meter event and will race for her first Olympic medal on Aug. 6.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Pierre grew up in Vermont on a family dairy, where she learned the value of hard work and determination.\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"score\": 0.98010368927767, \"rank\": 0.014972804955969777, \"text\": \"Vermont\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She developed a passion for running in High School and specializes in running long and middle-distance races.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Pierre still lives in Vermont on a dairy farm with her husband and young son, and when she's not training or helping with the cows, she is often promoting the dairy industry on her social media accounts, as well as attending events like World Dairy Expo.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 780, \"end\": 787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"score\": 0.98010368927767, \"rank\": 0.014972804955969777, \"text\": \"Vermont\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lacey Vilhauer can be reached at 620-227-1871 or[email\\u00a0protected].\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey_Von_Erich\", \"score\": 0.9409974376070694, \"rank\": 0.059523688897900225, \"text\": \"Lacey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey_Von_Erich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey_Von_Erich\"}]}]}"